<item>
            <title>[LU-4819] tests: Lustre Sanity test_101b hangs for large OSTCOUNTs</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4819</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Wizard appears to hang during test 101b of the Lustre Sanity test. There have been three instances of this type of hang on this particular system.&lt;br/&gt;
Xyratex-bug-id: MRP-1362&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;# ps aux | grep [r]eads
root     121602 99.9  0.0   4040   440 ?        R    Sep12 939:47 reads -f /tmp/tmpNmB5Fv/f101b -l 18432 -o 18304 -s 104857600 -b 1048576 -a 128 -n 0
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In all three instances the test logs appear to stop at test 101b:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;name: test_101a
            status: PASS
            duration: 1
            return_code: 0
            error:
        -
            name: test_101b
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Logs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== sanity test 101b: check stride-io mode read-ahead =================== 15:04:08 (1379023448)
error: set_param: /proc/{fs,sys}/{lnet,lustre}/obdfilter/*/read_cache_enable: Found no match
error: set_param: /proc/{fs,sys}/{lnet,lustre}/obdfilter/*/writethrough_cache_enable: Found no match
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
